        "Solves For Examples\n",
        "\n",
        "1)Write the equation of a sphere with center at point\n",
        "P\n",
        "=\n",
        "(\n",
        "1\n",
        ",\n",
        "2\n",
        ",\n",
        "3\n",
        ")\n",
        " and radius\n",
        "r\n",
        "=\n",
        "3\n",
        ".\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "**Answer**\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "(x - 1)Â² + (y - 2)Â² + (z - 3)Â² = 3Â²\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "2)Do the spheres with equations xÂ² + yÂ² + zÂ² = 1 and xÂ² + yÂ² + zÂ² = 2 have any common points?\n",
        "\n",
        "**No, they do not have any common points**\n",
        "\n",
        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "\n",
        "The equation xÂ² + yÂ² + zÂ² = 1 represents a sphere centered at the origin (0, 0, 0) with a radius of 1.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "The equation xÂ² + yÂ² + zÂ² = 2 represents a sphere centered at the origin (0, 0, 0) with a radius of âˆš2.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "Since the two spheres have the same center but different radii, they are concentric.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "Concentric spheres with different radii do not intersect, meaning they have no common points."
      ],
