        "3)What curve in space is formed by the intersection of the sphere xÂ² + yÂ² + zÂ² = 1 with the sphere (x - 1)Â² + yÂ² + zÂ² = 1 ? Find the equation of this curve.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "**to find the intersection, we need to solve the two equations**\n",
        "\n",
        "(x - 1)Â² + yÂ² + zÂ² - (xÂ² + yÂ² + zÂ²) = 1 - 1\n",
        "\n",
        "This simplifies to:\n",
        "\n",
        "(x - 1)Â² - xÂ² = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "Expanding and simplifying further, we get:\n",
        "\n",
        "xÂ² - 2x + 1 - xÂ² = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "-2x + 1 = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "x = 1/2\n",
        "\n",
        "**Substituting back**:\n",
        "\n",
        "Now that we have the value of x, we can substitute it back into either of the original equations to find the equation of the curve\n",
        "\n",
        "(1/2)Â² + yÂ² + zÂ² = 1\n",
        "\n",
        "1/4 + yÂ² + zÂ² = 1\n",
        "\n",
        "yÂ² + zÂ² = 3/4\n",
        "\n",
        "**Identifying the curve**: The equation yÂ² + zÂ² = 3/4 represents a circle in the yz-plane with a radius of âˆš(3/4) = âˆš3/2. Since x is fixed at 1/2, this circle is parallel to the yz-plane and is located at x = 1/2.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "**Therefore, the intersection of the two spheres is a circle with the equation**\n",
        "\n",
        " x = 1/2, yÂ² + zÂ² = 3/4."
